If you're still getting 8:26 after using the formula, it's possible that the original date string in cell B2 is not in the format that Excel is expecting.

You can check the format of the cell B2 by right-clicking on the cell, selecting "Format Cells...", and then going to the "Number" tab. If the format is not set to "Date", you can change it to "Date" and then specify the desired format (e.g. `MM/DD/YYYY hh:mm:ss AM/PM`).

Once the format of cell B2 is corrected, the formula should give you the correct result:
```
01/17/2023 12:26:31 PM
```
